14:28:02.050 [INFO] # Bulk processing and queueing frontmatter

14:28:02.050 [INFO] Use this schema when a task asks you to mark an existing note for later bulk processing or queueing.

14:28:02.050 [INFO] This file is the exact schema for the queueing marker. Workflow docs may tell you when to apply it, but the field contract lives here.

14:28:02.050 [INFO] Add YAML frontmatter like this:

14:28:02.050 [INFO] ```yaml
14:28:02.050 [INFO] ---
14:28:02.050 [INFO] bulk_processing_workflow: <workflow name>
14:28:02.050 [INFO] queue_batch_timestamp: <batch timestamp>
14:28:02.050 [INFO] queue_order_id: <order id>
14:28:02.050 [INFO] queue_state: <state>
14:28:02.050 [INFO] queue_target: <target>
14:28:02.050 [INFO] ---
14:28:02.050 [INFO] ```

14:28:02.050 [INFO] Batch fields:

14:28:02.050 [INFO] - `queue_batch_timestamp` is the batch creation timestamp taken from current time when the batch is prepared
14:28:02.050 [INFO] - every note in the same migration batch must carry the same `queue_batch_timestamp`
14:28:02.050 [INFO] - `queue_order_id` is a sortable integer position within that batch
14:28:02.050 [INFO] - compute `queue_order_id` after sorting the batch's file paths alphanumerically
14:28:02.050 [INFO] - within one batch, `queue_order_id` must form a contiguous sequence from `1` to `N`

14:28:02.050 [INFO] Queue state machine:

14:28:02.050 [INFO] - `pending` means the note has been queued for later processing and no processor has claimed it yet
14:28:02.050 [INFO] - `exporting` means a worker has claimed the note and is preparing or sending the source version into the destination system
14:28:02.050 [INFO] - `imported` means the destination system now has a candidate copy, but parity has not been checked yet
14:28:02.050 [INFO] - `verifying` means both sides exist and the migration process is checking structure, metadata, links, or attachments before calling it done
14:28:02.050 [INFO] - `migrated` means the destination copy is accepted as canonical and no divergence is currently known
14:28:02.050 [INFO] - `merge_conflict` means both sides were edited in incompatible ways during migration and a human or higher-level merge workflow must reconcile the content
14:28:02.050 [INFO] - `split_brain` means both systems now carry plausible but diverging active versions, and the process can no longer assume which side is authoritative
14:28:02.050 [INFO] - later workflows or tools may advance the state, but initial queueing starts at `pending` unless another schema says otherwise

14:28:02.050 [INFO] Common transitions:

14:28:02.050 [INFO] - `pending -> exporting` when a batch worker picks up the note
14:28:02.050 [INFO] - `exporting -> imported` when the target system successfully receives the first candidate copy
14:28:02.050 [INFO] - `imported -> verifying` when migration checks begin
14:28:02.050 [INFO] - `verifying -> migrated` when parity checks pass and the destination becomes the accepted copy
14:28:02.050 [INFO] - `verifying -> merge_conflict` when both copies changed and an automatic merge is not trustworthy
14:28:02.050 [INFO] - `verifying -> split_brain` when both systems continue accepting edits and authority is unclear
14:28:02.050 [INFO] - `merge_conflict -> verifying` after a reconciled version is written back and re-checked
14:28:02.050 [INFO] - `split_brain -> verifying` after one side is declared authoritative and the other side is realigned

14:28:02.050 [INFO] Required fields:

14:28:02.050 [INFO] - `bulk_processing_workflow` must be filled with the workflow identifier supplied by the relevant workflow doc
14:28:02.050 [INFO] - `queue_batch_timestamp` must be the current timestamp captured once for the whole batch when the note set is queued
