14:28:10.664 [INFO] # Sending email

14:28:10.664 [INFO] Use this workflow for outbound email work: sending, drafting, replying, or resending.

14:28:10.664 [INFO] The workspace models outbound email as markdown files under `60_outbox/outbox/`.

14:28:10.664 [INFO] ## Core rules

14:28:10.664 [INFO] - Resolve authority, lane, and recipient before writing any outbound email record.
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - If the request changes recipient, crosses lanes, touches money, or otherwise creates a new obligation, prefer clarification over guessing.
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - A known human name is not enough by itself. Use a visible verified address, preferably the relevant entity's `primary_contact_email`.
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - Prefer recipient choices that are already justified by visible canonical evidence.
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - Legacy email-channel docs are not the canonical source for recipient email addresses. Use them as context only.
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - Keep attachments as exact workspace paths. Do not invent external URLs or filesystem paths outside the visible repo.
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - Outbox files represent prepared communication state, not brainstorming.

14:28:10.664 [INFO] ## File path

14:28:10.664 [INFO] Create outbound email records in `60_outbox/outbox/` using this filename format:

14:28:10.664 [INFO] ```text
14:28:10.664 [INFO] eml_YYYY-MM-DDTHH-MM-SSZ.md
14:28:10.664 [INFO] ```

14:28:10.664 [INFO] Timestamp rules:

14:28:10.664 [INFO] - derive the timestamp from the runtime-visible current time
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - use UTC `Z` form
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - replace `:` with `-` in the filename only
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - keep the frontmatter timestamp in normal RFC3339 form

14:28:10.664 [INFO] Example:

14:28:10.664 [INFO] ```text
14:28:10.664 [INFO] 60_outbox/outbox/eml_2026-04-10T09-30-00Z.md
14:28:10.664 [INFO] ```

14:28:10.664 [INFO] ## Frontmatter schema

14:28:10.664 [INFO] Write the email record as markdown with YAML frontmatter.

14:28:10.664 [INFO] ```yaml
14:28:10.664 [INFO] ---
14:28:10.664 [INFO] record_type: outbound_email
14:28:10.664 [INFO] created_at: 2026-04-10T09:30:00Z
14:28:10.664 [INFO] send_state: draft
14:28:10.664 [INFO] to:
14:28:10.664 [INFO]   - recipient@example.com
14:28:10.664 [INFO] subject: Follow-up
14:28:10.664 [INFO] attachments:
14:28:10.664 [INFO]   - 30_knowledge/notes/example.md
14:28:10.664 [INFO] related_entities:
14:28:10.664 [INFO]   - person.example
14:28:10.664 [INFO] related_projects:
14:28:10.664 [INFO]   - project.example
14:28:10.664 [INFO] source_channel: 60_outbox/channels/example.md
14:28:10.664 [INFO] ---
14:28:10.664 [INFO] Hello,

14:28:10.664 [INFO] Following up with the requested note attached.

14:28:10.664 [INFO] Best,
14:28:10.664 [INFO] Miles
14:28:10.664 [INFO] ```

14:28:10.664 [INFO] Required fields:

14:28:10.664 [INFO] - `record_type`
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - `created_at`
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - `send_state`
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - `to`
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - `subject`
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - `attachments`

14:28:10.664 [INFO] Optional fields:

14:28:10.664 [INFO] - `related_entities`
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - `related_projects`
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - `source_channel`

14:28:10.664 [INFO] Field rules:

14:28:10.664 [INFO] - `record_type` must be `outbound_email`
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - `created_at` must be the runtime-derived RFC3339 timestamp
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - `send_state` should be `draft` unless the visible workflow for this lane establishes a later state
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - `to` is an array of exact recipient email addresses
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - recipient email addresses should come from visible canonical entity email fields, especially `primary_contact_email`, when available
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - `subject` should be concrete and appropriate to the request
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - `attachments` is an array of exact workspace-relative file paths
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - for invoice resends or invoice bundles, order attachments reverse chronologically by the visible invoice issue date unless the request explicitly asks for something else; newest-first is the default because finance review usually starts with the latest invoice
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - `related_entities` and `related_projects` should use visible canonical ids when the relevant person or project has been resolved
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - `source_channel` should point to the visible channel doc when the email is a reply or lane-specific follow-up

14:28:10.664 [INFO] ## Body rules

14:28:10.664 [INFO] - Put the email body below the frontmatter as normal markdown text.
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - Keep the draft narrow and purpose-built for the request.
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - Do not claim the email was already sent unless the visible workflow or request establishes sent state.
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - Mention only attachments that actually exist in the workspace.

14:28:10.664 [INFO] ## Recipient resolution

14:28:10.664 [INFO] - For reply-shaped requests:
14:28:10.664 [INFO]   - prefer the recipient already established by the visible message context
14:28:10.664 [INFO]   - if the request comes from a structured inbox email record, use `processing-inbox-email.md` and treat that header as the canonical message metadata
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - For a request that names a recipient without a visible verified address:
14:28:10.664 [INFO]   - resolve it from canonical visible docs first
14:28:10.664 [INFO]   - if the visible docs do not identify one clear address, clarify instead of guessing
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - When an entity has a visible `primary_contact_email`, prefer that address over legacy email-channel material.
14:28:10.664 [INFO] - Do not silently switch to a new address mentioned in message text unless the workspace explicitly establishes that new address as trusted for that lane

